01:04.040 --> 01:05.975
Cecilia: Mr. President,
you've been in office

01:06.009 --> 01:08.042
for less than a week,
and during that time,

01:08.044 --> 01:09.377
you've signed more executive orders

01:09.379 --> 01:11.647
than any other
administration in history.

01:11.681 --> 01:12.581
Why?

01:12.615 --> 01:14.501
Well, we have a great
deal of work to do.

01:14.504 --> 01:15.550
President Haas left us

01:15.552 --> 01:17.319
with a weak and fractured nation.

01:17.354 --> 01:18.821
And it will take sweeping changes

01:18.855 --> 01:19.755
to stem this tide.

01:19.789 --> 01:21.957
But my administration is up to the task.

01:21.983 --> 01:24.121
Let's talk about the first order...

01:24.133 --> 01:25.901
Somewhat controversial.

01:25.904 --> 01:27.638
<i>The "so-called" Muslim registry.</i>

01:27.641 --> 01:30.032
<i>And what's controversial about
keeping this country safe?</i>

01:30.066 --> 01:32.353
What exactly is your plan
<i>for implementation?</i>

01:32.356 --> 01:34.624
<i>Since you brought it before
the House a month ago,</i>

01:34.658 --> 01:36.592
its critics have only grown
<i>more vociferous.</i>

01:36.627 --> 01:38.127
<i>And its supporters, as well.</i>

01:38.161 --> 01:41.330
<i>And I would remind you that it passed</i>

01:41.365 --> 01:42.605
<i>before the President vetoed it.</i>

01:42.633 --> 01:44.233
<i>What we need to do, Cecilia,</i>

01:44.268 --> 01:46.302
<i>is clear out the
corrupt establishment.</i>

01:46.336 --> 01:48.233
<i>And I brought in individuals like, uh...</i>

01:48.236 --> 01:51.034
<i>Alice Winter, the
former CEO of Greypool,</i>

01:51.037 --> 01:52.430
<i>to be a part of my
national security team.</i>

01:52.432 --> 01:54.232
<i>And she's putting together a
list of would-be registrants</i>

01:54.234 --> 01:55.601
<i>as we speak.</i>

01:55.635 --> 01:56.868
<i>So, when the Congress...</i>

01:56.870 --> 01:58.537
<i>passes the registry officially,</i>

01:58.571 --> 02:00.038
we can hit the ground running.

02:00.073 --> 02:02.274
Look, it's the first
step in a long road.

02:02.308 --> 02:04.042
Really, I'm just getting started.

02:04.077 --> 02:06.877
You've also passed orders
to strengthen the military,

02:06.880 --> 02:08.275
increase border security,

02:08.277 --> 02:10.047
and you've asked
Defense Secretary Howell

02:10.049 --> 02:10.848
to draft a memo

02:10.883 --> 02:12.518
on how to defeat the Islamic Front.

02:12.552 --> 02:14.219
Can you talk more about that?

02:14.254 --> 02:16.053
We have never been more
vulnerable in this country

02:16.055 --> 02:17.122
than we are today.

02:17.157 --> 02:19.558
<i>We've suffered significant
intelligence failures,</i>

02:19.592 --> 02:20.792
<i>both foreign and domestic,</i>

02:20.827 --> 02:22.327
<i>under the Haas administration.</i>

02:22.362 --> 02:24.229
<i>The CIA failed to prevent</i>

02:24.264 --> 02:26.865
<i>an Islamic Front attack at the G20.</i>

02:26.900 --> 02:29.600
<i>And just a few days ago,
he FBI suffered an attack...</i>

02:29.602 --> 02:30.567
<i>in their own backyard.</i>

02:30.570 --> 02:32.504
You have to stop calling me.

02:32.507 --> 02:35.155
- And you have to get me out of here.
- Not possible.

02:35.158 --> 02:37.741
The FBI is doing random
sweeps on The Farm

02:37.744 --> 02:38.782
looking for you.

02:38.788 --> 02:40.086
You poke your head up for air,

02:40.089 --> 02:41.547
you'll be thrown in a hole so deep,

02:41.581 --> 02:42.681
no one will find you.

02:42.715 --> 02:46.051
How will you govern differently
<i>from President Haas?</i>

02:46.085 --> 02:48.220
<i>President Haas didn't
listen to the people.</i>

02:48.254 --> 02:49.988
<i>I do. It's that simple.</i>

02:50.023 --> 02:52.324
And what are the people
<i>saying to you now?</i>

02:52.358 --> 02:53.725
<i>They're saying, "Protect us.</i>

02:53.760 --> 02:55.527
<i>Make us feel safe."</i>

02:55.562 --> 02:56.995
<i>For too long,</i>

02:57.030 --> 02:58.730
<i>we've put our faith in corrupt leaders</i>

02:58.765 --> 03:00.165
<i>and a rigged system.</i>

03:00.200 --> 03:02.328
So, how do I fix this?

03:02.331 --> 03:03.765
Well, I have a proposal,

03:03.768 --> 03:06.071
and I'm gonna tell it
to you, Cecilia, first,

03:06.105 --> 03:07.105
right here and now.

03:07.140 --> 03:08.907
Really? I'm flattered.

03:08.942 --> 03:10.075
<i>I propose that we follow</i>

03:10.109 --> 03:12.211
<i>the lead of our founding fathers</i>

03:12.245 --> 03:14.580
<i>and amend the heart, mind,
and soul of our country.</i>

03:14.614 --> 03:17.583
Are you talking about calling
a Constitutional convention?

03:17.617 --> 03:18.684
<i>Yes, I am.</i>

03:18.718 --> 03:20.886
<i>For the second time in
this nation's history.</i>

03:20.920 --> 03:22.588
<i>It's time to take our system back,</i>

03:22.622 --> 03:24.957
<i>and be the America I know we can be.</i>

03:24.983 --> 03:26.407
<i>And it will require change,</i>

03:26.418 --> 03:31.029
<i>change today that will lead
us to a greater tomorrow.</i>

03:31.064 --> 03:32.631
Thank you, Mr. President.

03:32.665 --> 03:34.566
<i>No. Thank you, Cecilia.</i>

03:34.601 --> 03:37.402
[Beeping]

03:44.244 --> 03:46.578
[Keyboard clacking]

03:46.613 --> 03:49.615
[Beeping]

03:54.621 --> 03:56.421
♪

03:56.456 --> 03:58.060
Hey!

03:58.063 --> 03:59.291
Hey, listen up!

04:01.334 --> 04:02.894
The cache disappeared.

04:02.929 --> 04:04.096
Disappeared?

04:04.130 --> 04:05.931
It's gone. All of it.

04:05.965 --> 04:07.733
Been taken offline, I assume by Roarke.

04:07.767 --> 04:09.776
Ryan: And you're telling us because...

04:09.779 --> 04:11.669
you think we're just
gonna run in to that bunker

04:11.671 --> 04:12.704
and help you?

04:12.739 --> 04:14.640
I know things have been
fractured between us...

04:14.674 --> 04:15.707
[Laughs] Oh, yeah.

04:15.742 --> 04:17.308
Is that what you call
cutting out your entire team

04:17.310 --> 04:19.278
and trying to do the job yourself?

04:19.312 --> 04:21.413
How'd that work out? Okay.

04:23.549 --> 04:24.583
Raina?

04:24.617 --> 04:28.253
This team robbed me of a
chance to save my sister.

04:28.288 --> 04:30.689
And y-you didn't trust me then.

04:30.723 --> 04:31.890
How can I help you now?

04:33.026 --> 04:34.259
Ra...

04:38.197 --> 04:39.231
It's gone?

04:39.265 --> 04:41.724
- All the surveillance information?
- Owen: All of it.

04:41.727 --> 04:43.234
What, does that mean that it's over?

04:43.236 --> 04:44.735
It means they got whatever they needed

04:44.737 --> 04:46.017
for the last part of their plan.

04:46.039 --> 04:49.274
And we have no idea what that is.

04:49.309 --> 04:50.848
Roarke: No. Well, thank you.

04:50.851 --> 04:51.818
Thank you.

04:51.821 --> 04:53.376
Nice to see you. Pleasure.

04:53.379 --> 04:54.713
Not bad for a first sit-down,

04:54.747 --> 04:56.648
- don't you think?
- It's like you've been

04:56.683 --> 04:58.717
planning for it for
years, Mr. President.

04:58.751 --> 05:00.095
Well...

05:00.098 --> 05:01.398
Why did you ask me to come here?

05:01.401 --> 05:03.321
Well, just to let you
know you'd be rewarded

05:03.323 --> 05:04.790
for all the hard work you've done.

05:04.824 --> 05:06.625
Due to all your help
in the past few weeks,

05:06.659 --> 05:09.127
I'm finally able to reshape
our intelligence institutions.

05:09.162 --> 05:10.829
And, as someone who's done time in both,

05:10.863 --> 05:12.096
I think the country could benefit

05:12.098 --> 05:15.105
from your insight and your
expertise in that reshaping.

05:15.108 --> 05:17.302
The interview's over, Mr. President.

05:17.337 --> 05:19.671
You can speak directly.

05:19.706 --> 05:21.406
What do you want me to do?

05:21.441 --> 05:23.051
For your own safety,

05:23.054 --> 05:26.378
I think it's best you stay
insulated from the how,

05:26.412 --> 05:28.714
- as long as you know the when.
- And?

05:28.748 --> 05:30.415
Well, I'll just say this...

05:30.450 --> 05:33.218
I wouldn't leave town in
the next couple of days.

05:33.252 --> 05:34.720
[Chuckles softly]

05:36.622 --> 05:39.057
Shelby: It has been hours. Where is she?

05:39.092 --> 05:40.392
SDRs take time.

05:40.426 --> 05:42.727
Especially when you might be
watched by the man who carries

05:42.729 --> 05:43.861
the full weight of the
United States government

05:43.863 --> 05:44.596
behind you.

05:44.630 --> 05:46.365
She's... She's being thorough.

05:46.399 --> 05:48.734
Are we putting her in danger
by asking her to come here?

05:50.536 --> 05:52.070
We need her.

05:52.105 --> 05:53.171
[Door opens]

05:53.206 --> 05:56.464
Oh, thank God you're here.

05:56.467 --> 05:57.934
Hey. You lost your tails?

05:57.937 --> 05:59.444
About an hour ago.

05:59.478 --> 06:00.490
But I still changed cars

06:00.493 --> 06:02.395
one more time outside of Ewell.

06:02.398 --> 06:05.667
We couldn't rally the troops?

06:06.786 --> 06:09.287
Okay. What's going on there?

06:09.322 --> 06:11.176
The cache is gone, as
if it was never there.

06:11.179 --> 06:13.814
Any piece of intel, data,
pattern, state secrets...

06:13.817 --> 06:15.726
Because whatever they're about to do

06:15.728 --> 06:17.596
- is ready to go?
- Exactly.

06:17.630 --> 06:19.598
Three of us against who knows how many

06:19.632 --> 06:20.632
for the last stand?

06:20.666 --> 06:22.033
Not sure I like those odds.

06:22.068 --> 06:24.770
Owen: She's right. We need help.

06:24.804 --> 06:25.637
Then we get help.

06:25.671 --> 06:28.373
If we can't count on Raina and Ryan,

06:28.408 --> 06:31.109
we find friends that we can count on.

06:32.126 --> 06:35.781
And I was just hours away
from a trip to Mexico.

06:35.815 --> 06:38.216
And if anybody I worked
with knew I was here,

06:38.251 --> 06:40.819
I would've lost the job I
should have lost months ago.

06:40.853 --> 06:43.822
I've just been waiting by the phone.

06:43.856 --> 06:45.590
So this is the bunker?

06:45.625 --> 06:47.826
Only using 24% of the surface space.

06:47.860 --> 06:48.827
Power move.

06:48.861 --> 06:50.829
Miranda Shaw.

06:50.863 --> 06:52.798
We've not formally met.

06:52.832 --> 06:53.932
No.

06:53.966 --> 06:55.434
But I know a lot about you.

06:55.468 --> 06:57.569
Most of it wrong.

06:58.337 --> 07:00.806
Well, I don't know how
I feel about being here.

07:00.840 --> 07:02.140
[Sighs]

07:02.175 --> 07:03.442
They gave me no choice.

07:03.476 --> 07:04.509
[Chuckles] I know.

07:04.544 --> 07:05.343
To be honest,

07:05.378 --> 07:06.745
I had the first good night's sleep

07:06.779 --> 07:07.612
in about 30 years.

07:07.647 --> 07:09.658
I just had to turn off the television.

07:09.661 --> 07:11.704
Miranda: All right,
Alex, why are we here?

07:11.707 --> 07:13.338
And how much trouble
are we gonna get into?

07:13.340 --> 07:15.119
Because you know I
can't get into trouble.

07:15.121 --> 07:16.922
We're already in trouble, Miranda.

07:16.956 --> 07:18.523
With the cache gone,

07:18.558 --> 07:20.438
it's most likely the
first attack will be today.

07:20.460 --> 07:21.191
Will: D-Day.

07:21.194 --> 07:22.975
That was so much fun the first time.

07:22.978 --> 07:24.829
I've already almost
died twice this year.

07:24.831 --> 07:26.428
I'm not dying today.

07:26.431 --> 07:27.520
How can I help?

07:27.523 --> 07:30.469
Work to see why all of
this has been taken offline.

07:30.503 --> 07:31.703
I think the rest of us

07:31.737 --> 07:34.272
could analyze Roarke's executive orders,

07:34.307 --> 07:35.938
to see if they point to a greater plan.

07:35.941 --> 07:37.809
What?

07:37.844 --> 07:39.544
You asked me to help.

07:39.579 --> 07:40.612
I'm helping.

07:40.646 --> 07:41.945
Thank you.

07:41.948 --> 07:43.715
I may have been wrong about you, too.

07:43.749 --> 07:45.684
What are you waiting
for? Let's get to work.

07:45.718 --> 07:48.153
♪

07:48.187 --> 07:52.273
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

07:55.093 --> 07:57.171
Raina: We should have
stayed at the house.

07:57.174 --> 07:59.814
Ryan: We couldn't. They were
doing random sweeps.

07:59.848 --> 08:02.584
Why do you keep staring at them?

08:02.618 --> 08:04.630
Just watching Alex lead the B-team

08:04.633 --> 08:06.988
down yet another blind alley.

08:07.022 --> 08:09.075
You are a bitter, bitter man.

08:09.078 --> 08:10.712
Yeah, I don't see you out there.

08:10.715 --> 08:12.627
I have a real cause.

08:12.661 --> 08:14.395
Y-You just have a wounded heart.

08:14.430 --> 08:16.397
No. Don't get all The Ancient One on me,

08:16.432 --> 08:17.283
all right.

08:17.286 --> 08:18.800
I don't know what that is,

08:18.834 --> 08:22.236
and I know what you're really mad at.

08:22.271 --> 08:25.640
It's not Alex going off the road.

08:25.674 --> 08:28.242
It's who Alex went off-roading with.

08:29.678 --> 08:31.479
♪

08:31.513 --> 08:33.847
Alex: 30 executive orders in five days.

08:33.881 --> 08:36.476
And this one freezes
financial regulations

08:36.479 --> 08:37.717
until he can approve them.

08:37.720 --> 08:39.486
I mean, what's the endgame here?

08:39.520 --> 08:41.020
Fewer restrictions on banks.

08:41.023 --> 08:43.200
A hedge fund manager
wouldn't mind less regulation.

08:43.203 --> 08:45.337
- Yeah, but that doesn't relate to terrorism.
- No.

08:45.340 --> 08:48.075
Which means it wasn't
part of Roarke's plan.

08:48.078 --> 08:50.369
It's probably just a favor
for his friend Christian Kelly.

08:50.372 --> 08:51.504
Will: [Clears throat]

08:51.538 --> 08:54.040
Uh, judging from your
collective expressions,

08:54.074 --> 08:56.091
I'm about to interrupt
an important conversation.

08:56.094 --> 08:56.994
For that I'm sorry,

08:56.997 --> 08:59.178
but I have an equally
important question.

08:59.213 --> 09:01.180
Uh, can you tell me more

09:01.215 --> 09:02.882
about your operation in Cleveland?

09:02.916 --> 09:05.451
You went there because
one of the Collaborators

09:05.485 --> 09:07.420
got a piece of the cache, right?

09:07.454 --> 09:09.522
To threaten a judge and start a riot?

09:09.556 --> 09:11.357
Okay, Will, why don't we focus on

09:11.391 --> 09:13.392
finding who deleted the cache first,

09:13.427 --> 09:16.295
and then we can play
recent history, okay?

09:16.330 --> 09:18.030
Okay, good.

09:18.065 --> 09:19.765
If he keeps getting hung up on details,

09:19.800 --> 09:21.400
we're gonna be here till next week.

09:22.769 --> 09:24.303
What about this memorandum

09:24.338 --> 09:27.106
committing us to defeat
the Islamic Front?

09:27.140 --> 09:30.409
Maybe Roarke wanted to
stir up tensions overseas?

09:30.444 --> 09:33.446
Okay, what about... What about that one?

09:33.480 --> 09:34.947
[Cellphone vibrates]

09:35.849 --> 09:39.051
All right. Let's go back to this one.

09:39.086 --> 09:43.222
♪ Call it voyeurism or masochism ♪

09:43.257 --> 09:47.293
♪ I'm always watching you ♪

09:47.327 --> 09:50.129
Roarke's EO on increasing
border security...

09:50.163 --> 09:51.364
Any chance the Collaborators

09:51.398 --> 09:53.859
have an interest in exploiting
Mexican-American relations?

09:53.862 --> 09:56.168
Will: I-I know, I should
be focusing on the cache.

09:56.203 --> 09:58.237
But I was looking into the plane crash

09:58.272 --> 09:59.672
the Collaborators orchestrated,

09:59.706 --> 10:01.407
the one connected to Christian Kelly?

10:01.441 --> 10:04.243
Uh, The avionics
technology on the plane...

10:04.278 --> 10:05.177
We already know that.

10:05.212 --> 10:06.766
Kelly profited highly from

10:06.769 --> 10:08.537
the technology company's
rise after the crash.

10:08.539 --> 10:09.115
We know that.

10:09.149 --> 10:10.416
But what if the avionics system

10:10.450 --> 10:11.684
has another purpose?

10:11.718 --> 10:14.754
The crash caused avionics stock to rise,

10:14.788 --> 10:16.589
but there are easier ways to make money

10:16.623 --> 10:17.690
than crashing a plane.

10:17.724 --> 10:20.293
Are you saying that the
crash wasn't about the profit,

10:20.327 --> 10:21.594
but about the system itself?

10:21.628 --> 10:23.296
The government signed a contract

10:23.330 --> 10:25.197
with the company who
made it, ENGIN Industries,

10:25.232 --> 10:28.100
the day after the plane crash.

10:28.135 --> 10:30.102
Two commercial airlines followed suit.

10:30.137 --> 10:33.039
It's being added to all their
domestic 737s as we speak.

10:33.073 --> 10:34.507
When I left Roarke's office,

10:34.541 --> 10:37.043
he told me to "not leave town."

10:37.077 --> 10:38.341
Could that be a warning?

10:38.344 --> 10:40.686
Maybe the Collaborators
could use the system

10:40.689 --> 10:43.457
to actually take control of a plane.

10:43.460 --> 10:45.027
Or planes.

10:45.061 --> 10:46.128
If they do,

10:46.162 --> 10:48.497
this would be a terrorist
attack on a national scale

10:48.531 --> 10:51.500
that we haven't seen since 9/11.

10:51.534 --> 10:54.603
We're done with our time
out, if you'll have us back?

10:54.637 --> 10:55.971
Don't ask their permission.

10:56.005 --> 10:57.306
Fine. We're helping.

10:59.209 --> 11:01.109
Good to have you back.

11:04.854 --> 11:07.055
Will: This is the avionics technology,

11:07.058 --> 11:09.718
courtesy of the developers
at ENGIN Industries

11:09.752 --> 11:12.321
and their pitiful firewall.

11:12.355 --> 11:15.357
There's a line of code buried
in the emergency systems

11:15.391 --> 11:16.558
that could give someone

11:16.593 --> 11:18.727
remote control of the entire plane.

11:18.761 --> 11:21.071
That must be how they're
gonna hijack a plane or two.

11:21.074 --> 11:21.862
Yes.

11:21.865 --> 11:25.613
But commercial avionics don't
communicate with ground-based systems.

11:25.616 --> 11:26.716
For security purposes,

11:26.719 --> 11:28.678
they can only be accessed on board.

11:28.681 --> 11:29.615
What if you're on board

11:29.618 --> 11:32.341
with, like, a cellphone or a laptop?

11:32.375 --> 11:34.776
Could you access this
backdoor that way?

11:34.777 --> 11:35.565
Certainly.

11:35.568 --> 11:38.224
But you'd need a system
with exactly the right code.

11:38.227 --> 11:42.317
Peter Theo is one of the biggest
tech developers in the world.

11:42.352 --> 11:44.368
His apps are on millions of cellphones.

11:44.371 --> 11:46.321
Theo's biggest app, FundFriend,

11:46.356 --> 11:48.824
- just released an update last week.
- On it.

11:48.858 --> 11:51.350
What do you want to bet we're
gonna find a line of code

11:51.353 --> 11:53.929
that allows it to control
the avionics system?

11:53.963 --> 11:55.796
Did you ever imagine we'd
be working together someday

11:55.798 --> 11:57.298
back when you thought I was a bad guy?

11:57.300 --> 11:59.334
Who says you're a good guy?

12:00.737 --> 12:02.938
First, what I don't understand is,

12:02.972 --> 12:04.773
why hide the trigger in an app?

12:04.807 --> 12:05.841
Ryan: Security?

12:05.875 --> 12:06.941
If somebody accessed your phone,

12:06.943 --> 12:08.277
they wouldn't discover it.

12:08.311 --> 12:10.345
Miranda: No, no. Raina's right.

12:10.380 --> 12:13.282
FundFriend is the
biggest app to move money.

12:13.316 --> 12:16.184
Why hide a code in an
app that's used by...

12:16.219 --> 12:18.687
- 197 million people.
- Exactly.

12:18.721 --> 12:21.115
When only a handful of
suicide bombers need it?

12:21.118 --> 12:23.091
Unless they're not suicide bombers.

12:23.126 --> 12:25.627
I've been working trusted
Company sources and assets.

12:25.662 --> 12:27.029
No one's heard chatter

12:27.063 --> 12:29.131
of any terrorist event of any kind.

12:29.165 --> 12:30.689
So, how do you stage a terrorist event

12:30.692 --> 12:31.900
without terrorists?

12:31.935 --> 12:33.601
Raina: Who says they
have to be terrorists?

12:33.603 --> 12:35.938
They framed me without
me even being there.

12:35.972 --> 12:37.873
Maybe they're going
to use people's phones

12:37.907 --> 12:39.207
without them knowing?

12:39.242 --> 12:41.603
Turn unwitting
passengers into hijackers?

12:41.606 --> 12:42.744
They can use the app

12:42.779 --> 12:44.813
to make anyone they
want to into a terrorist.

12:44.847 --> 12:46.064
If that's true,

12:46.067 --> 12:47.946
we'd never be able to
find every passenger

12:47.949 --> 12:49.016
on a commercial flight today

12:49.018 --> 12:49.885
using FundFriend.

12:49.919 --> 12:51.653
That's... It's impossible.

12:51.688 --> 12:52.921
Excuse me.

12:53.523 --> 12:55.591
Alex: Let's re-look at this.

12:55.625 --> 12:56.658
[Cellphone clicking]

12:56.693 --> 12:57.626
[ <i>Rings</i> ]

12:57.660 --> 12:59.461
Clay: Now, look, I
already called Caleb back.

12:59.495 --> 13:02.517
I told him I'm fine,
so no need to worry.

13:02.520 --> 13:04.114
So, can you please stop calling?

13:04.117 --> 13:06.394
Because every time it rings,
I want to throw it out the window.

13:06.396 --> 13:07.803
You can put it on silent.

13:07.837 --> 13:10.322
Hmm. I'm waiting on a pizza.

13:10.325 --> 13:13.008
- Are you smoking?
- No.

13:13.042 --> 13:15.010
You are. You are smoking!

13:15.044 --> 13:16.612
And it isn't tobacco.

13:16.646 --> 13:18.580
Which is legal in D.C.
the last time I checked.

13:18.615 --> 13:19.513
Well, you're not in D.C.

13:19.515 --> 13:21.583
You're at the Hampton Court Motor Lodge

13:21.618 --> 13:23.151
in Springfield, Virginia,

13:23.186 --> 13:25.287
where possession is a misdemeanor.

13:25.328 --> 13:27.997
Are you calling me from 1955?

13:28.024 --> 13:29.958
I'm hanging up.

13:29.993 --> 13:31.593
You already tracked my phone,

13:31.628 --> 13:33.027
and my Sims are arguing in the kitchen.

13:33.029 --> 13:34.329
We need your help

13:34.364 --> 13:35.730
to narrow down the list of targets.

13:35.732 --> 13:36.498
If you were Roarke

13:36.532 --> 13:38.100
and you wanted to frame a passenger

13:38.134 --> 13:39.134
for blowing up a plane,

13:39.168 --> 13:40.369
who would you choose?

13:40.403 --> 13:43.105
Politically, someone
I'd want the country

13:43.139 --> 13:44.640
to think is a threat.

13:44.674 --> 13:45.974
Anyone from his registry.

13:46.009 --> 13:48.143
He tried to push it through again.

13:48.177 --> 13:49.645
It's still not popular.

13:49.679 --> 13:50.779
I don't know.

13:50.813 --> 13:53.281
What better way to frighten
people into getting on board

13:53.316 --> 13:55.283
than a terrorist attack
at the hands of a Muslim?

13:55.318 --> 13:56.718
God, that's what I was afraid of.

13:56.753 --> 13:58.687
Yeah, framing Raina for a mall bombing,

13:58.721 --> 13:59.788
that was a dry run.

13:59.822 --> 14:00.822
This is the main event.

14:00.857 --> 14:03.659
We need you. Your brain.

14:03.693 --> 14:04.866
Come back and help us.

14:04.869 --> 14:06.495
- [Cellphone beeps]
- Well...

14:06.529 --> 14:09.798
Yeah, uh, my pizza's here, so bye now.

14:10.600 --> 14:12.067
[Cellphone beeps]

14:15.071 --> 14:16.538
Alex: This is what we know so far.

14:16.572 --> 14:19.041
Roarke plans on hijacking
commercial planes,

14:19.075 --> 14:21.543
using unwitting Muslim passengers

14:21.577 --> 14:23.912
carrying Peter Theo's
FundFriend app on their phones.

14:23.946 --> 14:26.715
This way, they can hack into
the avionics system of the plane

14:26.749 --> 14:28.483
and bring them down.

14:28.518 --> 14:29.518
What we don't know

14:29.552 --> 14:31.586
- is which Muslims are being targeted.
- Right.

14:31.589 --> 14:34.222
Miranda: Even if we knew which
planes needed to be grounded,

14:34.257 --> 14:37.901
we still need specific
names to warn the pilots.

14:37.904 --> 14:40.194
We've got to find out who's
already on the registry.

14:40.196 --> 14:41.897
If the perpetrators are on there,

14:41.931 --> 14:43.843
it serves Roarke's policy.

14:43.846 --> 14:45.680
Who's got access?

14:46.269 --> 14:47.703
Alice Winter.

14:47.737 --> 14:49.271
- And I can get it.
- Owen: No way.

14:49.305 --> 14:50.905
- She'd kill you.
- And get yourself killed?

14:50.907 --> 14:53.061
Look, you can't risk blowing your cover.

14:53.064 --> 14:54.531
Your in with the Collaborators

14:54.534 --> 14:56.168
is our best hope of beating them.

14:56.171 --> 14:57.846
What... What if we fail today?

14:57.880 --> 14:59.781
We need them to still believe you.

14:59.816 --> 15:01.950
Okay, this is not up for discussion.

15:01.984 --> 15:04.386
And I know what I'm doing.

15:04.420 --> 15:07.122
And I don't need your permission.

15:07.156 --> 15:08.890
[Sighs]

15:08.925 --> 15:10.764
All right, fine.

15:10.775 --> 15:12.326
Miranda, Will and I will go to

15:12.329 --> 15:14.596
the FAA Command Center in Herndon.

15:14.630 --> 15:16.230
They'll have the resources
to ground these planes

15:16.232 --> 15:17.933
once we identify them.

15:17.967 --> 15:19.634
FAA personnel require

15:19.669 --> 15:21.436
an emergency call-and-response code

15:21.471 --> 15:22.421
to down a plane.

15:22.424 --> 15:23.805
Oh, let me guess...

15:23.840 --> 15:25.874
It's not a code that's given out freely?

15:25.908 --> 15:28.076
The President has it
and a couple of others,

15:28.111 --> 15:29.544
but that's it.

15:29.579 --> 15:32.314
Well, Claire's only been
out of power for a week.

15:32.348 --> 15:33.982
Shelby, does Clay have any connections

15:34.016 --> 15:35.117
he can still use?

15:35.151 --> 15:36.585
He might,

15:36.619 --> 15:39.821
but I don't think he'll
take another call from me.

15:39.856 --> 15:40.955
If I could see him in person,

15:40.957 --> 15:42.424
I might be able to convince him.

15:42.458 --> 15:44.659
You can't leave. Neither can I.

15:44.694 --> 15:46.094
The FBI would grab us on sight.

15:46.129 --> 15:47.576
Miranda: He's right.

15:47.579 --> 15:49.200
They're on the grounds as we speak.

15:49.203 --> 15:51.299
We have exactly zero minutes to waste.

15:51.334 --> 15:52.601
Look, the rest of you can go.

15:52.635 --> 15:54.936
Just not me, Shelby, or you, Raina.

15:54.971 --> 15:56.872
I know a way you can get out, Shelby.

15:59.876 --> 16:02.744
No one will tell me where my sister is.

16:02.779 --> 16:05.180
But I bet they'll take me to her.

16:08.117 --> 16:09.751
It's the only way.

16:11.220 --> 16:12.454
♪

16:15.625 --> 16:16.825
Agent: Stay where you are!

16:16.859 --> 16:19.294
May name is Raina Amin.

16:19.328 --> 16:23.598
My sister, Nimah Amin, was
taken wrongly into custody

16:23.633 --> 16:25.967
for an attack you believe
was perpetrated by me.

16:26.002 --> 16:27.435
Hands.

16:28.704 --> 16:30.839
Move.

16:31.240 --> 16:32.774
Let's go.

16:32.809 --> 16:35.811
♪

16:43.409 --> 16:44.786
Come on. Let's go.

16:44.821 --> 16:46.788
♪

16:50.600 --> 16:52.186
Keyes: All right, everyone.

16:52.189 --> 16:54.014
I know this isn't your first time,

16:54.017 --> 16:56.705
but we have no room for error here.

16:56.708 --> 16:58.209
We have passengers boarding planes

16:58.243 --> 16:59.577
who don't know their own phones

16:59.611 --> 17:01.012
are gonna turn them into hijackers.

17:01.046 --> 17:03.414
So, we need your best game.

17:03.449 --> 17:04.582
Where are we?

17:04.616 --> 17:06.416
In position at Greypool.

17:06.452 --> 17:08.151
I'll find out which
planes are being targeted

17:08.153 --> 17:09.854
and whose phones are
carrying out the hack.

17:11.810 --> 17:12.945
At Clay's hotel.

17:12.949 --> 17:14.925
I'll push him to lean on
his government contacts

17:14.926 --> 17:16.694
and get the emergency
call-and-response code

17:16.728 --> 17:18.896
we'll need to order
these planes to land.

17:18.931 --> 17:20.564
Woman: <i>As soon as everyone
has taken their seats,</i>

17:20.566 --> 17:21.631
<i>we will close the cabin door.</i>

17:21.633 --> 17:23.733
<i>You are free to use
your electronic devices</i>

17:23.769 --> 17:25.069
<i>until that time.</i>

17:28.774 --> 17:29.807
[Door closes]

17:29.842 --> 17:31.842
Miranda: Hey, we're almost
at the FAA Command Center.

17:31.844 --> 17:33.831
Once Alex gets the flight numbers,

17:33.834 --> 17:34.867
we'll radio the pilots.

17:34.870 --> 17:36.136
See if we can disable the hack

17:36.139 --> 17:37.606
and get them to land safely.

17:37.609 --> 17:38.716
Ryan: Copy.

17:38.750 --> 17:40.183
We're standing by to relay information

17:40.185 --> 17:41.686
to all the teams.

17:42.154 --> 17:44.188
Happy hunting. Good luck.

17:45.357 --> 17:47.158
I wasn't expecting to see you today.

17:47.192 --> 17:48.893
That's because no one sent for me.

17:48.927 --> 17:51.262
And yet I have a feeling
something's happening

17:51.296 --> 17:52.563
and I'm not a part of it.

17:52.598 --> 17:54.699
No, you're not.

17:56.159 --> 17:57.960
I betrayed everyone I know

17:57.963 --> 18:00.364
for a seat at this table, Alice.

18:00.806 --> 18:04.642
Don't give me a reason
to return the favor.

18:04.676 --> 18:07.512
I'll fill you in. With limits.

18:07.546 --> 18:08.626
Understood.

18:10.115 --> 18:12.174
Ryan: Look, time is
not on our side, Alex.

18:12.177 --> 18:13.751
Get those flights.

18:13.785 --> 18:14.986
Get those names.

18:18.891 --> 18:21.492
You're worried about her.

18:21.527 --> 18:22.860
I'm worried <i>for</i> her.

18:22.895 --> 18:23.794
There's a difference.

18:23.829 --> 18:26.264
Yeah, well...

18:26.298 --> 18:27.698
it took me years

18:27.733 --> 18:31.002
to trust that my wife
would come home safe.

18:31.036 --> 18:33.437
How long have you been married?

18:33.472 --> 18:35.273
31 years.

18:35.307 --> 18:36.236
And she's...

18:36.239 --> 18:39.277
The best darn operative
you'll never hear of.

18:39.311 --> 18:41.112
The only time she was home

18:41.146 --> 18:42.613
for more than a four-month stretch

18:42.648 --> 18:44.015
was to have our sons.

18:45.083 --> 18:46.817
- It's a good-looking family.
- Thanks.

18:46.852 --> 18:48.586
And you stay here?

18:48.589 --> 18:49.719
Take care of the kids?

18:49.721 --> 18:52.023
Hell, yes, I do.

18:52.057 --> 18:55.192
She's great at what she does,
and I'm great at what I do.

18:56.064 --> 18:57.598
See, when you find the right person,

18:57.601 --> 18:59.996
you don't worry that their
success takes away from you.

18:59.998 --> 19:01.732
You worry that you're not doing enough

19:01.767 --> 19:03.220
to help them be successful.

19:03.223 --> 19:04.051
[Chuckles]

19:04.054 --> 19:05.735
- Well, respectfully, sir...
- Why don't you screw the respect

19:05.737 --> 19:07.551
and speak your mind.

19:07.554 --> 19:10.174
Okay. I'm you in this narrative,

19:10.208 --> 19:12.043
- and she's...
- Exceptional.

19:12.077 --> 19:13.878
Then why send me to The Farm?

19:13.912 --> 19:15.045
Why would you put me in there

19:15.047 --> 19:17.815
if you knew she was "exceptional"?

19:17.849 --> 19:20.184
Quotes aren't helping your case, son.

19:20.218 --> 19:21.751
You want to know why
I sent you in there?

19:21.753 --> 19:23.020
To make her better.

19:23.055 --> 19:24.589
And you did. You challenged her.

19:24.623 --> 19:26.724
And she, not you, got us here today.

19:26.758 --> 19:29.026
[Scoffs]

19:29.061 --> 19:30.428
So that's my life?

19:30.462 --> 19:31.762
Challenging her?

19:31.797 --> 19:32.930
Making her better?

19:32.965 --> 19:34.732
Mm.

19:34.766 --> 19:38.669
My wife was worth the
cosmetic blow to my ego.

19:38.704 --> 19:41.772
Eventually, I realized I
was a better man for it.

19:41.807 --> 19:47.511
♪

19:47.546 --> 19:50.014
Shelby, what's your status?

19:50.048 --> 19:51.749
Clay? Clay?

19:51.783 --> 19:53.084
Hey, wake up.

19:53.118 --> 19:54.018
- Clay!
- Hey.

19:54.052 --> 19:55.052
Hi.

19:55.087 --> 19:57.254
Oh, of course it would be you.

19:57.289 --> 19:59.523
Listen, hundreds, maybe
thousands, of people

19:59.558 --> 20:00.558
are gonna die

20:00.592 --> 20:02.526
if you don't get us the
call-and-response code

20:02.561 --> 20:03.761
for airborne terror threats.

20:03.795 --> 20:06.752
- There's no such thing.
- Yes, there is.

20:06.755 --> 20:09.600
And we know that you can twist
the right arm and get it for us.

20:11.570 --> 20:13.371
You know, I can see
why people fall for you.

20:13.405 --> 20:15.906
[Scoffs]

20:15.941 --> 20:18.042
Sorry. Sorry.

20:18.076 --> 20:19.977
Here. Come back here.

20:20.012 --> 20:22.780
[Grunts]

20:22.814 --> 20:25.549
All I need you to do
is make one phone call.

20:25.584 --> 20:27.885
And all I need you to do...

20:27.919 --> 20:30.888
Clay! You... You are engaged!

20:30.922 --> 20:32.890
Not anymore.

20:33.592 --> 20:34.558
Oh, no.

20:34.593 --> 20:36.560
No. She left me.

20:36.595 --> 20:41.065
You know, once the bloom was
off the presidential rose,

20:41.099 --> 20:42.833
she got the hell out.

20:42.868 --> 20:45.803
She really left you?

20:45.837 --> 20:49.006
Yep.

20:49.041 --> 20:52.610
So, now I've got nothing.

20:52.644 --> 20:56.847
You know, except you,
here, in this moment.

20:56.882 --> 20:58.449
Why don't you figure out what you want,

20:58.483 --> 20:59.850
or you can go, too.

20:59.885 --> 21:03.320
I know what I want...

21:03.355 --> 21:07.591
For you to be a man and get us the code.

21:07.626 --> 21:09.593
I'm not leaving without it.

21:09.628 --> 21:10.795
♪

21:10.829 --> 21:11.929
Klein: I'm supervisor here.

21:11.963 --> 21:14.367
And this isn't normal
procedure for a terror threat.

21:14.370 --> 21:16.500
This isn't a normal threat.

21:16.535 --> 21:19.036
The FBI and the CIA
have fresh intelligence

21:19.071 --> 21:20.679
about imminent threats
to several flights

21:20.682 --> 21:21.890
that are already in the air.

21:21.893 --> 21:23.541
We need help identifying them.

21:23.590 --> 21:25.141
We need help grounding them.

21:25.144 --> 21:26.277
Klein: Wait here.

21:26.280 --> 21:29.248
[Sighs]

21:30.582 --> 21:31.549
Second thoughts?

21:31.583 --> 21:34.051
[Sighs] Déjà vu.

21:34.086 --> 21:37.488
I'm breaking the law to save the world.

21:37.522 --> 21:38.956
I just hope it works this time,

21:38.990 --> 21:40.196
and no one gets hurt,

21:40.199 --> 21:41.959
that we can just do it the right way.

21:41.993 --> 21:44.195
Doing what you think
is correct in the moment

21:44.229 --> 21:45.096
is the right way.

21:45.130 --> 21:46.754
Breaking the law can be the right way.

21:46.757 --> 21:48.231
You just have to not get caught.

21:48.233 --> 21:50.572
I've broken more federal laws
than both of you combined,

21:50.575 --> 21:52.703
and I've faced zero consequences.

21:52.738 --> 21:53.871
Klein: Special Agent Shaw?

21:53.905 --> 21:55.072
Right this way.

21:55.107 --> 21:57.174
♪

21:57.209 --> 21:59.243
So we cross-referenced
all the Muslim-Americans

21:59.277 --> 22:00.911
against anyone on a flight today

22:00.946 --> 22:02.680
who also had Peter's app on their phone.

22:02.714 --> 22:03.848
Six flights.

22:03.882 --> 22:05.850
One Muslim passenger from each flight

22:05.884 --> 22:07.384
on Roarke's registry.

22:07.419 --> 22:09.186
- Genius, isn't it?
- Wow.

22:09.221 --> 22:12.990
So, which flights? Passengers?

22:13.024 --> 22:14.191
Oh, come on.

22:14.226 --> 22:15.392
Haven't I earned...

22:15.427 --> 22:17.061
I think that's enough for today.

22:17.095 --> 22:18.513
We need those flights and those names.

22:18.515 --> 22:20.231
Whatever you think you should do, do it.

22:20.265 --> 22:21.398
I trust your judgment.

22:21.433 --> 22:23.025
My assistant can validate your...

22:23.028 --> 22:24.068
[Grunts]

22:24.102 --> 22:27.138
♪

22:35.147 --> 22:37.014
Getting flights and passengers.

22:37.017 --> 22:38.883
Incoming.

22:40.986 --> 22:42.753
The bad news is, I just lost a bet.

22:42.788 --> 22:44.588
I trusted you.

22:44.623 --> 22:46.090
Peter didn't.

22:46.124 --> 22:47.958
The good news is,

22:47.993 --> 22:49.627
now I get to take it out on you.

22:49.661 --> 22:51.195
Bring it.

22:54.606 --> 22:56.560
We have the flight
numbers. Acknowledged.

22:56.563 --> 22:58.966
They're all in the air. Just
took off not 5 minutes ago.

22:58.968 --> 23:00.736
Once those planes reach 30,000 feet

23:00.770 --> 23:02.237
and the Wi-Fi signal turns on,

23:02.271 --> 23:03.972
the passengers's phones will connect

23:04.007 --> 23:05.866
to whoever's behind this on the ground.

23:05.869 --> 23:08.170
How can we ground those
planes before that happens?

23:10.446 --> 23:12.447
TransWestern six-four-four,
this is FAA Command.

23:12.482 --> 23:13.482
Do you copy?

23:13.516 --> 23:16.651
Man: D.C., this is
six-four-four-kilo-zulu. Copy.

23:16.686 --> 23:19.121
Return and begin emergency
landing procedure,

23:19.155 --> 23:20.288
runway three.

23:20.323 --> 23:21.089
Copy.

23:21.124 --> 23:23.091
TransWestern six-four-four. Copy.

23:24.961 --> 23:27.281
They're not changing
course. Something's off.

23:27.284 --> 23:29.312
TransWestern six-four-four, I repeat,

23:29.315 --> 23:31.696
return and begin emergency
landing procedure,

23:31.699 --> 23:32.699
runway three.

23:32.702 --> 23:33.879
- Do you copy?
- Copy.

23:33.882 --> 23:36.233
Look. The signal latency is nonexistent.

23:36.236 --> 23:38.170
If we were speaking
to a flight miles away,

23:38.173 --> 23:39.973
there would be a tiny, measurable delay

23:39.976 --> 23:41.743
in our communications, but there isn't.

23:41.778 --> 23:43.493
Because we're not
speaking to the pilots,

23:43.496 --> 23:45.080
we're speaking to someone nearby

23:45.114 --> 23:46.426
who has commandeered the channel.

23:46.428 --> 23:48.211
The pilots think they're speaking to us,

23:48.214 --> 23:49.983
but instead, they're speaking to him.

23:49.986 --> 23:52.407
If we can't find out
who and where they are,

23:52.410 --> 23:54.423
we can't stop all this.

23:54.457 --> 23:56.425
Man #1: 10,000 feet and climbing.

23:56.459 --> 23:57.725
Man #2: <i>The captain will let you know</i>

23:57.727 --> 23:59.193
<i>when it's safe to move about the cabin.</i>

23:59.195 --> 24:00.262
[Bell dings]

24:03.800 --> 24:06.401
[Both grunting]

24:10.964 --> 24:13.208
Will, how's that location coming?

24:13.242 --> 24:15.710
Will: I've calculated a
radius based on the latency

24:15.745 --> 24:17.372
to identify the location of those

24:17.375 --> 24:19.276
spoofing the planes' communications.

24:19.279 --> 24:21.817
Sending a signal at such
a significant distance

24:21.851 --> 24:23.825
would require an antenna and radio mast

24:23.828 --> 24:25.920
- large enough to...
- Skip the story.

24:25.922 --> 24:27.389
Just give us the twenty.

24:27.423 --> 24:29.172
I'll text them to you now.

24:29.175 --> 24:30.309
Man #2: <i>Just a reminder</i>

24:30.312 --> 24:32.059
<i>to stay in your seats with
your seatbelts fastened</i>

24:32.061 --> 24:34.729
<i>until the captain has turned
off the seatbelt sign.</i>

24:34.764 --> 24:37.125
Shelby, once Miranda
and Owen get that twenty,

24:37.128 --> 24:38.128
we need that code.

24:38.131 --> 24:39.468
I'm trying my best here.

24:39.478 --> 24:41.855
Clay, there is no other
way to ground these flights.

24:41.858 --> 24:43.426
They will go down without it.

24:43.429 --> 24:46.128
Keyes: Will confirms the
first flight is at 30,000 feet.

24:46.131 --> 24:47.701
Wi-Fi's been switched on.

24:47.704 --> 24:49.612
Woman: <i>The captain has indicated
that you are now free</i>

24:49.614 --> 24:50.714
<i>to use your approved electronic devices.</i>

24:50.716 --> 24:53.620
Clay: We're all going down
anyway, sooner or later.

24:53.623 --> 24:55.891
Sooner... Sooner and later?

24:55.894 --> 24:57.252
Sooner <i>than</i> later?

24:57.286 --> 24:59.387
Please! Clay?

25:01.097 --> 25:02.824
[Groans]

25:03.059 --> 25:05.875
[Engine starts]

25:05.878 --> 25:08.395
Man #3: Reston tower, this
is TransWestern six-four-four.

25:08.397 --> 25:11.032
Our plane has switched to
autopilot on its own. Copy.

25:11.067 --> 25:12.934
Man #4: TransWestern six-four-four,

25:12.969 --> 25:14.936
we'll look into that and
get back you you, copy.

25:14.971 --> 25:17.239
Get the message to
Theo that it's working.

25:17.273 --> 25:19.541
- The first flight's under control.
- Okay.

25:19.575 --> 25:22.298
The first flight is under our control.

25:22.358 --> 25:25.527
♪

25:25.561 --> 25:27.061
2,000 lives are at stake.

25:27.096 --> 25:31.599
2,000 people are going to
die if you don't help us.

25:31.634 --> 25:35.236
Don't prioritize your
pride over their lives.

25:37.039 --> 25:38.540
Sorry.

25:41.443 --> 25:43.278
I'm so sorry.

25:43.312 --> 25:46.948
Hey, yeah, I need a favor...

25:46.982 --> 25:48.917
Man #4: Pan Atlantic
flight five-five-four,

25:48.951 --> 25:52.253
turn left, heading three-two-zero.

25:52.288 --> 25:54.155
Freeze! FBI! Stand down!

25:59.595 --> 26:00.862
Owen: Stay down.

26:00.896 --> 26:02.597
Miranda; TransWestern six-four-four,

26:02.631 --> 26:05.033
your tower communication
has been comprised.

26:05.067 --> 26:06.935
This is Special Agent Miranda Shaw.

26:06.969 --> 26:08.489
Stand by for presidential access code.

26:08.504 --> 26:13.274
Zulu-Juliet-Quebec-eight-six-Victor.

26:13.309 --> 26:16.211
Zulu-Juliet-Quebec-eight-six-Victor.

26:16.245 --> 26:19.280
I need you to initiate
emergency landing protocol

26:19.315 --> 26:20.648
overriding autopilot,

26:20.683 --> 26:22.450
and confiscate and destroy

26:22.484 --> 26:24.385
the mobile phone of a passenger.

26:24.420 --> 26:25.887
Keyes: Aasim Samaan, 12-C.

26:25.921 --> 26:27.555
Owen: Aasim Samaan, 12-C.

26:27.590 --> 26:29.591
Miranda: Aasim Samaan, 12-C.

26:29.625 --> 26:31.893
Khan, K. Sunbeam flight one-one-two

26:31.927 --> 26:33.461
- seat 5-A.
- Rashad Radhi,

26:33.495 --> 26:35.230
Southeastern flight three-three-five,

26:35.264 --> 26:36.631
- seat 10-E. Udin Y.,
- CoastWest

26:36.665 --> 26:38.566
- flight four-zero-three, seat 14B.
- Satara G.,

26:38.601 --> 26:40.468
Pan Atlantic flight
five-five-four, seat 35-B.

26:40.502 --> 26:42.670
Ryan: Next plane is
Southeastern sixteen.

26:42.705 --> 26:44.771
Southeastern sixteen, this
is CIA operative Owen Hall.

26:44.773 --> 26:46.441
Initiate emergency landing response

26:46.475 --> 26:47.674
- on the following code.
- Keys: Southeastern sixteen...

26:47.676 --> 26:48.943
Will: All targeted flights

26:48.978 --> 26:50.618
are beginning emergency
landing procedure.

26:52.014 --> 26:53.248
[Exhales deeply]

26:57.286 --> 26:58.620
Whew.

26:58.654 --> 27:01.840
[Laughs]

27:01.843 --> 27:03.010
Alex: Hey.

27:04.693 --> 27:07.161
[Sighs] Bad news.

27:07.196 --> 27:08.529
All six of those planes

27:08.564 --> 27:10.632
are on their way to landing safely.

27:10.666 --> 27:12.333
No one lost their lives,

27:12.368 --> 27:14.535
including all those
innocent Muslim men and women

27:14.570 --> 27:15.870
you tried to frame.

27:15.905 --> 27:17.205
So, it's over, Alice.

27:17.239 --> 27:19.374
For you.

27:19.408 --> 27:21.175
Once President Roarke and the others

27:21.210 --> 27:23.278
find out that you were
working against us,

27:23.312 --> 27:24.712
I'll ask for the privilege

27:24.747 --> 27:27.348
of being the one to take you out myself.

27:27.383 --> 27:29.350
I look forward to it.

27:29.385 --> 27:31.502
This isn't over. You
only think you've won.

27:32.321 --> 27:34.088
[Door opens, closes]

27:36.616 --> 27:38.967
Keyes: Congratulations.

27:39.002 --> 27:41.191
What looks like a
travel headache for some

27:41.194 --> 27:43.839
is in reality a thwarted massacre

27:43.873 --> 27:45.173
for the entire country.

27:45.208 --> 27:47.142
Countless people are alive

27:47.176 --> 27:49.378
because of everyone in this room.

27:49.427 --> 27:52.562
And, like always, no
one will know that truth.

27:52.582 --> 27:55.050
The sacrifice heroes make.

27:55.084 --> 27:56.245
Miranda: That's the secret you learn

27:56.247 --> 27:58.186
when you do it enough times, right?

27:58.221 --> 28:01.189
What, is that what we are? Heroes?

28:01.224 --> 28:03.258
I don't feel any different.

28:03.293 --> 28:04.925
Alex: Well, that's the
other secret you learn.

28:04.927 --> 28:07.424
It's still always just a Tuesday.

28:07.427 --> 28:09.363
Owen: Hey, this doesn't mean it's over.

28:09.365 --> 28:10.398
Roarke is still President.

28:10.400 --> 28:11.533
The Collaborators are alive,

28:11.567 --> 28:13.068
and the world is none the wiser.

28:13.102 --> 28:15.270
And they will most certainly find a way

28:15.305 --> 28:17.372
to retaliate against us
for foiling their plans.

28:17.407 --> 28:18.774
Indeed.

28:18.808 --> 28:20.108
But, until then,

28:20.143 --> 28:25.013
let's take a moment
to bask in the victory.

28:25.048 --> 28:26.448
Okay, moment's over.

28:26.482 --> 28:27.916
There's still work to be done.

28:27.950 --> 28:29.683
You've got a presidency to topple.

28:29.686 --> 28:31.887
And we still don't know how.

28:31.921 --> 28:33.789
[Sighs] You can't leave.

28:33.823 --> 28:36.625
Nimah and Raina are both in custody.

28:36.659 --> 28:40.228
Alice Winter... She
knows I turned on them.

28:40.263 --> 28:43.198
I feel like this is the part

28:43.232 --> 28:46.601
where I need to give a rousing speech.

28:46.636 --> 28:49.237
But all I can think of is... thank you.

28:50.626 --> 28:53.261
We would not have been
able to do this without you.

28:55.645 --> 28:57.879
And we wouldn't be here without you.

28:59.615 --> 29:02.017
Thanks. I'll let him know.

29:05.154 --> 29:07.322
- What happened?
- All the flights landed.

29:07.357 --> 29:09.257
The FAA hasn't made a statement yet,

29:09.292 --> 29:10.926
but everyone is safe.

29:10.960 --> 29:13.929
Well, glad I could help.

29:13.963 --> 29:15.564
You want to really help?

29:15.598 --> 29:16.665
Take off those pity pants,

29:16.699 --> 29:18.266
come back to the bunker with me,

29:18.301 --> 29:20.502
and do your job.

29:20.536 --> 29:21.636
Pity pants?

29:23.180 --> 29:24.748
My mom used to say that.

29:24.774 --> 29:27.342
My mom used to say,

29:27.377 --> 29:29.344
"Get your head out of your ass, Clay.

29:29.379 --> 29:32.147
I can't give a speech about
gun control at the NRA."

29:32.181 --> 29:32.948
Huh?

29:34.083 --> 29:36.485
I might still be a little bit drunk.

29:37.887 --> 29:39.621
Come back.

29:39.655 --> 29:41.690
Do what you were meant to do.

29:41.724 --> 29:44.793
How is it you know what's best for me?

29:44.827 --> 29:47.095
Oh, it's because I'm smarter than you.

29:47.130 --> 29:48.587
I know more words than you.

29:48.590 --> 29:50.532
I have more emotions than you.

29:50.566 --> 29:51.800
I have them.

29:51.834 --> 29:53.635
I just don't let you know I have them.

29:53.669 --> 29:56.037
♪

29:56.072 --> 29:57.472
I'm having one right now.

29:58.141 --> 30:00.542
It's a complicated one.

30:00.576 --> 30:02.144
It's like 10 at once.

30:04.080 --> 30:06.047
She really left you?

30:06.082 --> 30:08.417
She was gonna leave me anyway.

30:09.986 --> 30:11.153
[Whispers] Don't.

30:12.355 --> 30:13.688
Don't come any closer.

30:14.724 --> 30:17.159
[Exhales sharply]

30:17.193 --> 30:18.326
[Pounding on door]

30:18.361 --> 30:19.995
Man: FBI! Open up!

30:21.030 --> 30:23.576
A spy drinking Scotch?

30:23.579 --> 30:24.499
[Laughing]

30:24.534 --> 30:27.202
- That's a little cliché, Owen.
- Yeah.

30:27.236 --> 30:29.196
I know you didn't come
here to insult me, did you?

30:29.205 --> 30:30.872
No, I can do that
plenty behind your back.

30:30.907 --> 30:33.008
[Laughs]

30:33.042 --> 30:37.179
I came here because
of something you said

30:37.213 --> 30:39.681
about doing the right
thing in the moment.

30:39.715 --> 30:43.852
You know, I often forget how much faith

30:43.886 --> 30:48.423
the Bureau and the Agency put in us.

30:48.458 --> 30:50.192
They choose us,

30:50.226 --> 30:52.327
they put us through all these tests,

30:52.361 --> 30:54.563
evaluating not just
our bodies, our minds,

30:54.597 --> 30:57.532
but our morality,

30:57.567 --> 31:02.537
our decisiveness, our judgment.

31:02.572 --> 31:05.407
I have to stop

31:05.441 --> 31:08.543
trying to make up for my past.

31:08.578 --> 31:10.679
I made choices.

31:10.713 --> 31:13.348
I can't undo them.
There's no real penance.

31:13.382 --> 31:16.751
I just have to adapt and move forward.

31:16.786 --> 31:18.753
I see that now.

31:18.788 --> 31:20.789
And I think...

31:20.823 --> 31:25.393
I think that you should see that, too.

31:29.432 --> 31:32.067
If you're talking about my daughter,

31:32.101 --> 31:34.903
about choices I made as a father,

31:34.937 --> 31:39.641
then sure, maybe there's
no penance to be had.

31:39.683 --> 31:42.418
But it doesn't mean I stop trying to...

31:42.445 --> 31:43.745
make up for my failures,

31:43.779 --> 31:45.981
stop trying to do better.

31:46.015 --> 31:49.484
I'm not saying you stop trying.

31:49.519 --> 31:51.319
I'm saying you stop hating yourself

31:51.354 --> 31:53.455
when you fail sometimes.

31:53.489 --> 31:55.757
That's how you stay in it.

31:55.791 --> 31:57.459
You have to move on.

31:59.195 --> 32:00.962
[Cellphone vibrates]

32:04.967 --> 32:06.768
What? What's wrong?

32:08.049 --> 32:09.783
- [Knock on door]
- Alex: Yep.

32:13.309 --> 32:15.510
You hear the one about the
operative who went undercover

32:15.545 --> 32:17.579
inside the most dangerous
and powerful conspiracy

32:17.613 --> 32:19.014
in this nation's history?

32:19.048 --> 32:20.248
No, I haven't.

32:20.283 --> 32:21.555
How does it end?

32:21.558 --> 32:23.826
Well, no one's heard
it, so I don't know.

32:27.490 --> 32:30.091
[Sighs]

32:30.126 --> 32:33.061
We beat them today.

32:34.230 --> 32:35.297
Yeah.

32:37.366 --> 32:40.368
What about tomorrow?

32:40.403 --> 32:42.437
Or tonight...

32:42.471 --> 32:44.439
when they come for me?

32:44.473 --> 32:45.974
Look.

32:46.008 --> 32:48.777
We're all behind you, Alex.

32:48.811 --> 32:50.345
We're not going anywhere.

32:53.249 --> 32:55.116
You're still sexy when you lie.

32:55.151 --> 32:56.851
Uh, I'm not lying.

32:56.886 --> 32:58.453
<i>This</i> time.

32:58.456 --> 32:59.851
- I'm not.
- You're still sexy.

32:59.854 --> 33:00.654
Yeah, well...

33:00.657 --> 33:02.591
[Both laugh]

33:04.860 --> 33:05.961
You know...

33:08.364 --> 33:11.366
you're a great leader, Alex.

33:11.400 --> 33:14.502
You... You see the big picture.

33:14.537 --> 33:16.404
And me? I'm...

33:16.439 --> 33:18.573
I'm a great soldier.

33:18.608 --> 33:20.509
You send me into battle,
and I focus on that.

33:20.512 --> 33:21.346
I mean, I...

33:22.378 --> 33:23.712
I get lost in it.

33:23.746 --> 33:25.280
But you, you...

33:27.917 --> 33:31.086
You see everything.

33:31.120 --> 33:35.056
And I did the same thing
in our relationship.

33:35.091 --> 33:38.560
Every choice that you
made, I felt in the moment,

33:38.594 --> 33:41.196
whereas you...

33:41.230 --> 33:45.400
You were thinking long-term.

33:45.417 --> 33:47.947
I mean, maybe if I wasn't
so shortsighted, we Ryan.

33:48.904 --> 33:50.372
Stop.

33:50.406 --> 33:52.374
This is where we are.

33:54.243 --> 33:55.577
This is where we are.

33:56.045 --> 33:58.246
Owen: Alex? Ryan?

33:58.280 --> 34:00.448
They're here. We've been made.

34:00.483 --> 34:01.549
How long do we have?

34:01.584 --> 34:03.892
Man: FBI! Come out! FBI!

34:03.895 --> 34:05.120
We got them.

34:05.154 --> 34:08.422
Special Agent Shaw?
What are you doing here?

34:08.456 --> 34:11.592
I'm with them.

34:11.627 --> 34:14.295
I thought there was no
such thing as penance.

34:14.330 --> 34:15.630
I felt it in the moment.

34:15.665 --> 34:18.041
Okay, this doesn't have to be a scene.

34:18.043 --> 34:19.600
We will go with you quietly.

34:19.601 --> 34:20.601
I think you're confused.

34:20.636 --> 34:22.036
We're not here to arrest you.

34:22.071 --> 34:22.937
You're not?

34:22.972 --> 34:24.405
You're coming with us.

34:24.408 --> 34:25.873
The President wants to see you.

34:25.908 --> 34:27.043
All of you.

34:27.045 --> 34:29.141
♪

34:33.159 --> 34:34.958
Roarke: Too often, when a President

34:34.962 --> 34:37.781
has to talk to Americans
about acts of terrorism,

34:37.784 --> 34:39.850
it's with a heavy heart.

34:39.853 --> 34:45.091
But, today, I stand before
you without that heavy heart.

34:45.125 --> 34:47.460
And while the threat of radicals

34:47.494 --> 34:49.431
is never far from our front door,

34:49.434 --> 34:50.629
today, it didn't make it.

34:50.630 --> 34:52.398
There was almost a
terrorist attack today.

34:52.431 --> 34:57.136
But it was stopped by a
group of FBI and CIA agents

34:57.170 --> 34:59.005
working on an off-book mission

34:59.039 --> 35:01.474
to protect our country
from its greatest threat...

35:01.508 --> 35:03.442
Those who hate us for our freedoms.

35:03.477 --> 35:05.111
The world is safer

35:05.145 --> 35:07.513
because of the acts of
this group of brave souls.

35:07.547 --> 35:10.116
And while they work in the shadows,

35:10.150 --> 35:12.585
I believe you should know their faces

35:12.619 --> 35:15.154
and applaud them for their heroism.

35:15.188 --> 35:17.816
[Applause]

35:17.819 --> 35:19.858
Now, these are the
very same men and women

35:19.860 --> 35:21.793
that helped bring an end
to the G20 hostage crisis

35:21.795 --> 35:23.029
last September,

35:23.063 --> 35:25.197
which, recent intelligence revealed,

35:25.232 --> 35:27.466
was not an act of outside force,

35:27.501 --> 35:30.775
but an internal battle
between our own agencies.

35:30.778 --> 35:32.569
We live in divided times.

35:32.572 --> 35:35.641
But the time for that divide is over.

35:35.676 --> 35:37.843
Today the FBI and the CIA

35:37.878 --> 35:41.405
worked together to help
keep our country safe.

35:41.408 --> 35:44.150
Now, this was your mother's legacy.

35:44.184 --> 35:46.852
And I commend her for
blazing this trail...

35:46.887 --> 35:49.221
Seeing that we work stronger together,

35:49.256 --> 35:50.957
instead of against one another.

35:50.991 --> 35:52.892
So, we will not only rebuild

35:52.926 --> 35:56.128
both our intelligence
agencies from scratch,

35:56.163 --> 35:57.897
we will combine them to help rebuild

35:57.931 --> 36:00.199
the faith and trust
of the American people.

36:00.233 --> 36:01.634
It's time our country unites,

36:01.668 --> 36:03.469
and the Constitutional convention

36:03.503 --> 36:04.737
in 100 days

36:04.771 --> 36:08.207
will be a bold step in that process.

36:08.241 --> 36:11.043
We not only can be safe and free,

36:11.078 --> 36:12.411
we will be.

36:12.446 --> 36:14.380
We are the United States of America,

36:14.414 --> 36:16.194
and we hold our freedoms close.

36:16.197 --> 36:17.316
We protect them.

36:17.351 --> 36:20.720
We must always be the
land of opportunity

36:20.754 --> 36:22.555
and the land of peace.

36:22.589 --> 36:24.255
Woman: Mr. President, how long...

36:24.257 --> 36:26.859
Instead of silencing us,
he's using us as an example,

36:26.893 --> 36:29.161
to dismantle the FBI and the CIA.

36:29.196 --> 36:30.529
Give himself all the power.

36:30.564 --> 36:31.931
It's from crashing?

36:31.934 --> 36:33.946
Well, he'd have torn
down the CIA and the FBI

36:33.949 --> 36:35.352
<i>because</i> we failed.

36:35.360 --> 36:36.928
This was always the plan.

36:36.963 --> 36:38.230
He was covered either way.

36:38.264 --> 36:39.831
We're heroes, we're villains.

36:39.866 --> 36:41.099
He still wins.

36:41.134 --> 36:43.402
He spins our success into his victory.

36:43.436 --> 36:45.337
The perfect politician.

36:45.371 --> 36:47.939
Thank you.

36:47.974 --> 36:49.941
Thank you.

36:49.976 --> 36:51.510
Thank you.

36:51.544 --> 36:53.345
Thank you. Thank you.

36:53.379 --> 36:55.387
- Thanks.
- Ryan: Mm-hmm.

36:55.390 --> 36:57.758
Thanks.

36:57.761 --> 36:59.418
Mm.

36:59.452 --> 37:01.639
♪ One part of me wants to run ♪

37:01.642 --> 37:04.222
You have a nice smile,
you know that, Alex?

37:04.257 --> 37:06.124
Nice trick, Mr. President.

37:06.159 --> 37:08.293
You use us and then you own us.

37:08.327 --> 37:10.561
Well, if your team wants
to stay employed and alive,

37:10.563 --> 37:12.297
then I guess I do own you.

37:12.331 --> 37:15.634
I'm sure Alice has told you
which side I'm really on.

37:15.668 --> 37:18.370
Well, you don't need
to worry about Alice.

37:18.404 --> 37:20.205
She knew that the work we were doing

37:20.239 --> 37:22.708
might result in a sacrifice
for the greater good.

37:22.742 --> 37:26.144
- You had her killed?
- Hmm.

37:26.179 --> 37:28.413
You want to make me into a monster.

37:28.448 --> 37:31.116
But, you know, really, we're the same.

37:31.150 --> 37:33.452
You don't like to be bound by rules.

37:33.486 --> 37:36.254
You trust your moral
compass, I trust mine.

37:36.289 --> 37:39.124
I enjoy having you on my team, Alex.

37:39.158 --> 37:40.292
I'll see you soon.

37:40.326 --> 37:42.627
♪ Take all of me once ♪

37:42.662 --> 37:45.163
♪ Take all of me twice ♪

37:45.198 --> 37:46.398
What are you doing?

37:48.167 --> 37:49.835
I don't work here anymore.

37:49.869 --> 37:50.702
Hmm.

37:50.737 --> 37:52.938
Tell that to the <i>New York Post.</i>

37:52.972 --> 37:54.573
"Biparti-saint!

37:54.614 --> 37:56.769
President Roarke unites the states."

37:56.772 --> 37:57.772
They talk all about

37:57.775 --> 37:59.543
how the former President's
own son and strategist

37:59.545 --> 38:00.751
helped him.

38:00.754 --> 38:03.181
POLITICO even thinks it was your idea.

38:03.216 --> 38:07.185
[Scoffs]

38:07.220 --> 38:08.787
What's gonna happen?

38:08.821 --> 38:10.856
Yeah, that's usually what I ask.

38:10.890 --> 38:12.591
I used to have the answer.

38:13.826 --> 38:15.093
We're gonna get him.

38:15.128 --> 38:16.294
He's unimpeachable.

38:16.329 --> 38:17.410
Truly.

38:17.413 --> 38:19.063
He's been in the game so long,

38:19.065 --> 38:20.599
he sees every play.

38:20.633 --> 38:22.133
There's no way to get
ahead of him enough

38:22.135 --> 38:23.168
to see him coming.

38:23.202 --> 38:24.876
What was all this for?

38:24.879 --> 38:26.804
Because it... It can't just be about

38:26.806 --> 38:28.373
getting rid of the FBI and the CIA.

38:28.407 --> 38:29.508
Stop.

38:29.542 --> 38:31.376
Breathe.

38:31.410 --> 38:32.410
Let your mind rest.

38:32.445 --> 38:34.880
We won't see anything
if you're all wound up.

38:34.914 --> 38:36.681
I'm not wound up.

38:36.716 --> 38:37.936
I'm just sober, finally.

38:37.939 --> 38:40.841
Yeah, well, you still
need to take a moment.

38:40.844 --> 38:42.911
And if I'm being honest,

38:42.914 --> 38:45.323
I kind of need one, too.

38:45.358 --> 38:49.227
♪ Have I wanted something more ♪

38:49.262 --> 38:50.695
Thank you.

38:52.865 --> 38:54.366
♪ Take all of me once ♪

38:54.400 --> 38:56.568
I'm sorry I made a pass at you.

38:56.602 --> 38:59.871
I'm sorry Maxine left you.

38:59.906 --> 39:02.307
♪ Talk all of me stupid ♪

39:02.341 --> 39:04.743
Do you maybe want to
grab a burger somewhere?

39:04.777 --> 39:05.926
What, now?

39:05.929 --> 39:08.480
It'd be nice get out from underground.

39:08.514 --> 39:10.248
If Rome's gonna burn around us,

39:10.283 --> 39:13.552
I'd like to see it one last time.

39:13.586 --> 39:17.389
And I'd like to see it with you.

39:17.423 --> 39:20.392
Miranda: Hey, I think you
all may want to see this.

39:20.426 --> 39:24.196
♪ Not far to the good stuff ♪

39:24.230 --> 39:25.330
- Hmm.
- Yeah.

39:25.364 --> 39:30.702
♪ As the crow flies ♪

39:33.090 --> 39:34.257
And I was gonna say yes.

39:34.260 --> 39:35.841
Cecilia: <i>President Roarke's proposal</i>

39:35.875 --> 39:38.677
<i>of combining and
re-branding the FBI and CIA</i>

39:38.711 --> 39:40.111
<i>will apparently require</i>

39:40.146 --> 39:42.581
<i>a new amendment to the
United States Constitution.</i>

39:42.615 --> 39:44.916
<i>This idea has emboldened
many delegates</i>

39:44.951 --> 39:46.751
<i>to support the Constitutional convention</i>

39:46.786 --> 39:48.353
<i>Roarke's been calling for.</i>

39:48.387 --> 39:50.255
<i>Though an official vote
of state legislatures</i>

39:50.289 --> 39:52.357
<i>is scheduled to commence
tomorrow morning,</i>

39:52.391 --> 39:53.959
<i>we have numerous reports</i>

39:53.993 --> 39:56.394
<i>of various states, once resistant,</i>

39:56.429 --> 39:58.309
<i>now showing their full
support for a convention.</i>

39:58.331 --> 39:59.598
<i>Among them...</i>

39:59.632 --> 40:01.800
<i>Florida, Texas, Georgia,</i>

40:01.834 --> 40:05.136
<i>Wisconsin, Ohio, Michigan,
and Pennsylvania.</i>

40:05.171 --> 40:06.605
<i>And we also have varying reports</i>

40:06.639 --> 40:08.139
<i>that up to 18 more</i>

40:08.174 --> 40:09.773
<i>will announce their
intent to participate</i>

40:09.775 --> 40:11.276
<i>well ahead of the required deadline.</i>

40:11.310 --> 40:14.412
<i>This is an unprecedented
display of national unity</i>

40:14.447 --> 40:16.481
<i>in a country that just a few weeks ago</i>

40:16.515 --> 40:17.829
<i>was considered by most</i>

40:17.832 --> 40:19.718
<i>to be more divided
than it ever had been</i>

40:19.752 --> 40:20.785
<i>under the administration</i>

40:20.820 --> 40:22.319
of former President Claire
Haas <i>and Ronald Todd.</i>

40:22.321 --> 40:23.421
I can't watch this.

40:23.456 --> 40:24.990
<i>Unnamed sources do confirm</i>

40:25.024 --> 40:26.992
<i>that the state legislature of Virginia</i>

40:27.026 --> 40:29.127
<i>was going to come out
against the convention,</i>

40:29.161 --> 40:31.496
<i>but we've been told that
Senator Lewis Baynard</i>

40:31.530 --> 40:33.064
<i>acted as an intermediary</i>

40:33.099 --> 40:35.300
<i>in persuading his home
state to agree to take part.</i>

40:35.334 --> 40:38.069
<i>Baynard was singled out and
thanked by President Roarke</i>

40:38.072 --> 40:38.977
<i>in a st...</i>

40:38.980 --> 40:40.337
Well, at least we have the answer

40:40.339 --> 40:42.607
as to the role Senator
Baynard played in this.

40:42.642 --> 40:44.375
The Collaborators must've
called in their favor

40:44.377 --> 40:46.611
from his fake news incident
to get Virginia onboard.

40:46.646 --> 40:48.013
Shelby: Will was right.

40:48.047 --> 40:49.514
They were the perfect machine.

40:49.548 --> 40:52.117
Every move they made,
every calculated step,

40:52.151 --> 40:54.352
it all fit together
and resulted in this...

40:54.387 --> 40:56.354
What it's been about the entire time.

40:56.389 --> 40:58.857
A Constitutional
convention is an invitation

40:58.891 --> 41:00.458
to rewrite the law wholesale

41:00.493 --> 41:02.277
and change the face of this country.

41:02.280 --> 41:05.096
And America is welcoming
it with open arms.

41:05.131 --> 41:06.831
What are we gonna do about it?

41:06.866 --> 41:08.414
Well, there's no running from this.

41:08.417 --> 41:09.502
That's for sure.

41:09.535 --> 41:11.503
When Roarke exposed us on TV,

41:11.537 --> 41:13.805
you all joined my ranks.

41:13.839 --> 41:15.507
Burned as operatives to every

41:15.541 --> 41:18.009
foreign intelligence
service in the world.

41:18.044 --> 41:19.511
None of us are safe anywhere.

41:19.545 --> 41:20.946
Shelby: Including here.

41:20.980 --> 41:23.515
Which is why we fight back. We resist.

41:23.549 --> 41:25.383
No. No, you heard Miranda.

41:25.418 --> 41:26.818
The people want this.

41:26.852 --> 41:28.153
This was a... a feeling

41:28.187 --> 41:29.562
that's been lying
dormant in this country.

41:29.564 --> 41:32.021
A dying spark that now
has gasoline poured on it,

41:32.024 --> 41:33.391
turning it into a burning flame,

41:33.426 --> 41:34.893
lighting the way towards an America

41:34.927 --> 41:37.462
no one in this room
would even recognize.

41:37.496 --> 41:40.198
No. If we resist, then
we become the villains.

41:40.232 --> 41:41.866
We can't win that way.

41:41.901 --> 41:43.134
Alex: Owen's right.

41:43.169 --> 41:46.037
We have to be patient.

41:46.072 --> 41:48.506
We have to make Roarke
believe that we're on his side.

41:48.541 --> 41:50.342
He's always played the long game.

41:50.376 --> 41:52.310
We never did.

41:52.345 --> 41:54.746
This is our last
chance, our only chance.

41:54.780 --> 41:57.148
We have to strike
when the time is right.

41:57.183 --> 41:59.584
When is the convention, Clay?

41:59.618 --> 42:01.486
100 days from now.

42:02.323 --> 42:03.722
That's when we attack.

42:05.831 --> 42:09.302
So, who wants to be a terrorist?

